cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on recognizing surgical activities using deep learning models, which involves analyzing and processing visual data from surgical videos. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely category as the paper specifically focuses on robot-assisted minimally invasive surgery. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses deep learning models for surgical activity recognition. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper involves developing an automated system for surgical activity recognition. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing and processing multimedia data (surgical videos) using deep learning models.
